    "body":  "**Goal:**\nVisually simulate a real-time compliance alert system by adding a banner to the Dashboard. This enhances perceived value and reinforces IMQ’s focus on compliance readiness.\n\n**Requested Change:**\n1. Add a banner-style alert message on the Dashboard page\n\n- Position: Right side of the screen, horizontally aligned with the existing Dashboard page title and tagline (\"Track, assess, and prove worker qualifications in regulated environments\")\n- Behavior: Only visible when alerts exist (for now, always visible with placeholder text)\n- Sample Text:\n⚠️ 3 unresolved compliance alerts\n\n\n2. Make the banner appear clickable (button-style or underline-on-hover)\n\n- For now, no click behavior is required (simulate interactivity only)\n\n3. Design Hints (for Copilot):\n\n- Use a warning color like #ffc107 (Bootstrap warning yellow) or a light red\n- Keep height minimal (~40px or less)\n- Add a margin below the banner before the tiles begin\n\n4. Future Behavior (Do not implement yet):\n\n- Will eventually filter alerts relevant to the logged-in user\u0027s scope (team, org, or admin)\n- Clicking the banner will navigate to a full “Compliance Alerts” page\n\n**Note to Dev Team:**\n\n- This is a UI-only simulation — no backend filtering or alert calculation yet\n- This will help us showcase audit awareness and system readiness in LinkedIn demos",
